The paper discusses the use of convolutional networks to create a model of an individual's personal preferences based on rated photos, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of deep learning models for this task also falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the noise in attractiveness labels, which suggests the use of information retrieval techniques (cs.IR) to handle this issue. Finally, the paper discusses the success of dating apps, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
